Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Rainbow trout (_Oncorhynchus mykiss_) / ** / 0 / ** / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
** Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: Samples were taken in the pool in the frame of screening activities.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; surveillance outside infected and/or protection zone; surveillance within infected and/or protection zone; screening; quarantine; official disposal of carcasses, by-products, and waste; selective killing and disposal; zoning; killing for commercial use or own use; disinfection; process to inactivate the pathogenic agent in products or by-products; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: screening

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

